 As for Sarai thy wife, thou shalt not call her name Sarai, but Sarah shall her name be’). This has been one of the most enduringly popular girls' names."],"variants":[{"name":"Sara","meanings":["Variant of   Sarah .  This is the form used in the Greek of the New Testament (Hebrews 11:11)."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":25,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705191,"age":50,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705192,"age":63,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705193,"age":72,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705195,"age":117,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":